SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 0512222696 'Red/red-manual/changes.html' &&
  chmod 0640 'Red/red-manual/changes.html' ||
  echo 'restore of Red/red-manual/changes.html failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Red/red-manual/changes.html'`"
  test 9348 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Red/red-manual/changes.html: original size 9348, current size $shar_count"
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
fi
# ============= Red/red-manual/customisation.html ==============
if test -f 'Red/red-manual/customisation.html' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Red/red-manual/customisation.html (file already exists)'
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
else
  > _sharnew.tmp
  echo 'x - extracting Red/red-manual/customisation.html (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Red/red-manual/customisation.html' &&
X<html>
X<head>
X<title>Red: Customisation</title>
X<link rev="made" href="mailto:mik@cs.su.oz.au">
X</head>
X
X<body bgcolor=white>
X
X<center>
X<table>
X<tr>
X	<td valign=top> <IMG SRC="red-logo.GIF" ALT="RED" > </td>
X	<td> <font size=+3>Customisation</font> </td>
X</tr>
X</table>
X</center>
X
X<hr>
XThe possibilities to make changes to Red fall in two categories:
X<OL>
X	<LI> Changes made by an individual user.
X	<LI> Red setup (typically done by an administrator).
X</OL>
XRed lets users make their individual changes interactively, while the system
Xsetup is done by writing X resources.<p>
XThis chapter is devided into several sections:
X<OL>
X	<LI><A HREF="#preferences">Preferences</A>
X	<LI><A HREF="#bindings">Key Bindings</A>
X	<LI><A HREF="#toolbar">Changing the Toolbar</A>
X	<LI><A HREF="#fonts">Changing Fonts</A>
X	<LI><A HREF="#colours">Changing Colours</A>
X	<LI><A HREF="#resources">X Resources</A>
X</OL>
X
X<hr>
X
X<A NAME="preferences"><h3>1. Preferences</h3></A>
X
XTo change the Red preferences, choose <strong>Preferences...</strong> from the
XOptions menu.<p>
X
XThe preferences are:
X
X<blockquote>
X<DL>
X  <DT> <strong>Show toolbar</strong>
X	<DD> Toggles the display of the toolbar.
X
X  <DT> <strong>Beep with warnings</strong>
X	<DD> Determines whether Red beeps when displaying a warning.
X
X  <DT> <strong>Make backup when saving</strong>
X	<DD> When on, Red automatically creates a backup file when an existing
X	file is changed.  The backup file name has a <strong>.~</strong> 
X	suffix.
X
X  <DT> <strong>Remember window locations over sessions</strong>
X	<DD> Not yet implemented.
X</DL>
X</blockquote>
X
XPreferences are saved as soon as they are defined and retained for future
Xsessions.  They are stored in a file named ".red-prefs" in the user's
Xhome directory.
X
X<A NAME="bindings"><h3>2. Key Bindings</h3></A>
X
XChanging key bindings allows a user to change the function that is called
Xby a given key.  Several keys can call the same function.  All keys can be
Xcombined with one or more of the three modifier keys <em>Shift, Control, 
XAlt</em>.  A maximum of two modifier keys is recognised for each key 
Xcombination.<p>
X
XTo view or change the key bindings, call 
X<A HREF="func-custom.html#key-bindings">key-bindings</A> (by default on Alt-k
Xand in the Options menu).  This opens a dialog.  
X
X<UL>
X    <LI>Choose a category from the <em>Categories</em> menu to see the 
X	functions in each group.
X    <LI>Select a function in the function list to see a description of the
X	function and its key bindings.
X    <LI>Click on <em> Add Key</em> and press a key combination to add a key
X	to the keys that call the function currently selected.
X    <LI>Select a key in the key list and press <em>Delete Key</em> to remove
X	this key from the list of keys that call the function currently 
X	selected.
X</UL>
X
XThe <em>Defaults</em> button can be used to revert the key bindings to their
Xdefault values.  <em>This operation can not be undone!</em><p>
X
XThe key bindings are stored in a file named ".red-key-bindings" in the user's
Xhome directory.  Removing this file causes Red to revert to default bindings.
XA set of key bindings can be given to another user by copying this file into
Xthe user's home directory.
X
X<A NAME="toolbar"><h3>3. Changing the Toolbar</h3></A>
X
XChanging the toolbar is not yet implemented.
X
X<A NAME="fonts"><h3>4. Changing Fonts</h3></A>
X
XChanging fonts interactively is not yet implemented.
X
X<A NAME="colours"><h3>5. Changing Colours</h3></A>
X
XChanging colours is not yet implemented.
X
X<A NAME="resources"><h3>6. X Resources</h3></A>
X
XAlthough it might be confusing, the class name to use for changing some Red 
Xresources is <em>Blue</em>.  This is, because Red is part of the Blue
Xprogramming environment (which has not yet been released), and resources
Xfor that environment are for the resource class <em>Blue</em>.  Some 
Xresources are for the class <em>Red</em>.<p>
X
XImplementation of X resources is not yet complete.  Here are some, that you 
Xcan use already (to use them, add the line to your X resources database).<p>
X
X<DL>
X<DT><strong>Blue.editFont: <em>font</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>The default font used for editing.</em><p>
X	Examples:
X	<blockquote>
X		Blue.editFont:	lucidasanstypewriter-12<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	lucidasanstypewriter-14<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	lucidasanstypewriter-bold-12<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	lucidasanstypewriter-bold-14<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	8x13<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	8x13bold<br>
X		Blue.editFont:	9x15
X	</blockquote>
X	The font must be a fixed character width font.<p>
X
X<DT><strong>Blue.infoFont: <em>font</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>The default font used in the information area.</em><p>
X	Example:
X	<blockquote>
X		Blue.infoFont:	*menu*12*
X	</blockquote>
X	<p>
X
X<DT><strong>Red.width: <em>pixels</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>Initial width of the Red window in pixels. (Default: 688)</em>
X	<p>
X
X<DT><strong>Red.height: <em>pixels</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>Initial height of the Red window in pixels. (Default: 500)</em>
X	<p>
X
X<DT><strong>Blue.manBrowser: <em>path</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>The full path of the WWW browser to be used to display this 
X	manual.</em><p>
X
X<DT><strong>Blue.manURL: <em>URL</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>The URL of the online manual.</em><p>
X
X<DT><strong>Blue.motd1: <em>text</em></strong>
X<DT><strong>Blue.motd2: <em>text</em></strong>
X	<DD><em>Message of the day: Line one and two of a text to be displayed
X	    in the information area at startup.</em><p>
X
X</DL>
X
X<hr>
X  <A HREF="red-main-page.html">
X  <IMG SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" border=0 align=middle >Main index</A>
X
X</body>
X</html>
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 0512222696 'Red/red-manual/customisation.html' &&
  chmod 0640 'Red/red-manual/customisation.html' ||
  echo 'restore of Red/red-manual/customisation.html failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Red/red-manual/customisation.html'`"
  test 5520 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Red/red-manual/customisation.html: original size 5520, current size $shar_count"
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
fi
# ============= Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html ==============
if test -f 'Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html (file already exists)'
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
else
  > _sharnew.tmp
  echo 'x - extracting Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html' &&
X<html>
X<head>
X<title>Red: Cut, Copy and Paste</title>
X<link rev="made" href="mailto:mik@cs.su.oz.au">
X</head>
X
X<body bgcolor=white>
X
X<center>
X<table>
X<tr>
X	<td valign=top> <IMG SRC="red-logo.GIF" ALT="RED" > </td>
X	<td> <font size=+3>Cut, Copy and Paste</font> </td>
X</tr>
X</table>
X</center>
X
X<hr>
X
X<A NAME="selections"><h3>1 How to make a selection</h3></A>
X
XCut and paste commands are closely connected to selections in the text, so 
Xfirst I'll say a few words about selections. <p>
X
XSelections can be made both with the mouse or with keys.
X
X<h4>1.1 Selecting with the mouse</h4>
X
XSelections can be made using the mouse by
X
X<ul>
X	<li> dragging (that is: clicking and holding) with the left mouse
X	button over the text to be selected
X
X	<li> clicking with the first mouse button at the start of the text
X	to be selected (setting the cursor), then clicking with the right 
X	mouse button at the end
X
X	<li> double click on a word to select that word
X
X	<li> triple click on a line to select that line
X
X	<li> continue clicking after a triple click to select additional lines
X
X	<li> continue clicking after a double click with the shift key held
X	down to select additional words
X</ul>
X
X<h4>1.2 Selecting with keys</h4>
X
X<ul>
X
X	<li> To select a word, use <A HREF="func-edit.html#select-word">
X	select-word</A>.
X
X	<li> To select a line, use <A HREF="func-edit.html#select-line">
X	select-line</A>.
X
X	<li> To select an arbitrary region of text, move the cursor to the
X	beginning of the text you want to select, then use 
X	<A HREF="func-misc.html#set-mark">set-mark</A> to set a mark at that 
X	position.  After that, move the cursor to the end of the text to be 
X	selected and use <A HREF="func-edit.html#select-region">
X	select-region</A> to select the region between the mark and the cursor.
X</ul>
X
XAny selection function that is called while a selection is already on, <strong>
Xadds</strong> to the current selection rather than replacing it.
X
X<h3>2 Copy</h3>
X
XThere is no separate copy operation in Red.  Some systems, such as the MacOS,
Xrequire the call of an explicit copy to transfer the selected text into the 
Xinternal paste buffer.<p>
X
XRed follows the X Windows style: as soon as text is selected, it is available 
Xfor pasting.  No explicit copy operation is needed.  Text can be copied by
Xjust selecting and pasting it.
X
X<h3>3 Cut</h3>
X
X<A HREF="func-edit.html#cut">Cut</A> removes the selection from the text and
Xplaces it into the paste buffer.
XActually, since the text is placed into the paste buffer as soon as it is 
Xselected, cut just removes the selection from the text (doing exactly the same
Xthing as the delete or backspace key when a selection is on).
X
XThe reason that a separate cut function exist, is purely for later extensions,
Xwhen Red will hold a stack of paste buffers.
X
XSome different cut functions are available.  Some of them require text to
Xbe selected first, others don't.  All text that is cut, whether it was selected
Xor not, is placed into the paste buffer.
X
X<ul>
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut">cut</A> cuts the current selection.
X
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut-word">cut-word</A> cuts the complete
X	word the cursor is in.
X
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut-to-end-of-word">cut-to-end-of-word</A>
X	cuts the text from the cursor position to the end of the current word.
X
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut-line">cut-line</A> cuts the currnt 
X	line.
X
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut-to-end-of-line">cut-to-end-of-line</A>
X	cuts the text from the cursor position to the end of the current line.
X
X	<li><A HREF="func-edit.html#cut-region">cut-region</A> cuts the text
X	from the mark (see <A HREF="func-misc.html#set-mark">set-mark</A>) to
X	the cursor position.
X</ul>
X
XOnly for <em>cut</em> must the selection be on.  All other functions can be
Xcalled without setting a selection.
X
X<h4>3.1 Collecting Cuttings</h4>
X
XMost of the time, cutting some text replaces the previous text in the paste 
Xbuffer.  There is an exception: when two cut functions are called in straight
Xsuccession (no other function is used inbetween) the second cut <strong>adds
X</strong> to the cut buffer.<p>
X
XUsing this technique, several lines, for instance, can be moved easily.  You can
Xcall <em>cut-line</em> several time in a row to place <em>all</em> the lines
Xinto the paste buffer, move the cursor to the destination position, and then
Xcall <em>paste</em>.
X
X<h3>4 Paste</h3>
X
X<A HREF="func-edit.html#paste">Paste</A> pastes the current paste buffer at the
Xcursor position.  It can be called by using the middle mouse button (place 
Xcursor and paste), or by keys.  If a selection is on when calling paste, the
Xcontents of the paste buffer replace the current selection.<p>
X
XThe current paste buffer contains the text last cut or selected <em>in any
XX application</em> (not only Red).  You can select text in a terminal window 
Xand paste it into Red.
X
X<hr>
X  <A HREF="red-main-page.html">
X  <IMG SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" border=0 align=middle >Main index</A>
X
X</body>
X</html>
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 0512222696 'Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html' &&
  chmod 0640 'Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html' ||
  echo 'restore of Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html'`"
  test 4988 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Red/red-manual/cut-paste.html: original size 4988, current size $shar_count"
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
fi
