  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Red/red-manual/func-help.html' &&
X<html>
X<head>
X<TITLE>Red Help Functions</TITLE>
X</head>
X
X<body bgcolor=white>
X
X<center>
X <IMG SRC="red-logo.GIF" ALT="RED" > 
X	<font size=+3>Reference: Help Functions</font>
X</center>
X
X<HR>
X
X<A HREF="red-main-page.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>M</font>AIN <font size=+1>I</font>NDEX</A>
X
X<A HREF="function-group.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>F</font>UNCTION <font size=+1>O</font>VERVIEW</A>
X
X<p>
X<A HREF="func-edit.html"><font size=+1>E</font>DIT</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-move.html"><font size=+1>M</font>OVE&<font size=-1>S</font>CROLL</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-file.html"><font size=+1>F</font>ILE</A>  
X<A HREF="func-custom.html"><font size=+1>C</font>USTOMISATION  
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/left.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT=""></A>  
X<strong><font size=+1>H</font>ELP </strong>
X<A HREF="func-misc.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/right.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>M</font>ISC.</A> 
X
X<HR>
X
X
X<DL>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="show-manual">show-manual</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Help
X<P>
X<DD>Shows the online manual for Red (the manual you are reading just now).
XThe manual is an HTML document and a WWW browser is started to display it.  
XThe default browser is Netscape, but this can be changed using Red's X 
Xresources (see <A HREF="customisation.html#resources">X Resources</a> in 
Xthe Customisation section).
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="describe-key">describe-key</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-d
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Help
X<P>
X<DD>Prints out the name of the function called by a key.  After calling
Xdescribe-key, press the key you are interested in and the associated
Xfunction will be shown in the information area.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="key-bindings">key-bindings</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-k
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Options
X<P>
X<DD>This function is described in the customisation group, since it 
Xallows to change key bindings to 
Xpersonal preferences.  But it is also useful as a help function, since it
Xdisplays key bindings and short function explanations.  See 
X<A HREF="func-custom.html#key-bindings">customisation functions:
Xkey-bindings</A>.
X
X</DL>
X<HR>
X
X<A HREF="func-edit.html"><font size=+1>E</font>DIT</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-move.html"><font size=+1>M</font>OVE&<font size=-1>S</font>CROLL</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-file.html"><font size=+1>F</font>ILE</A>  
X<A HREF="func-custom.html"><font size=+1>C</font>USTOMISATION  
