# ============= Red/red-manual/func-misc.html ==============
if test -f 'Red/red-manual/func-misc.html' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Red/red-manual/func-misc.html (file already exists)'
  rm -f _sharnew.tmp
else
  > _sharnew.tmp
  echo 'x - extracting Red/red-manual/func-misc.html (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Red/red-manual/func-misc.html' &&
X<html>
X<head>
X<TITLE>Red Misc. Functions</TITLE>
X</head>
X
X<body bgcolor=white>
X
X<center>
X <IMG SRC="red-logo.GIF" ALT="RED" > 
X	<font size=+3>Reference: Misc. Functions</font>
X</center>
X
X<HR>
X
X<A HREF="red-main-page.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>M</font>AIN <font size=+1>I</font>NDEX</A>
X
X<A HREF="function-group.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>F</font>UNCTION <font size=+1>O</font>VERVIEW</A>
X
X<p>
X<A HREF="func-edit.html"><font size=+1>E</font>DIT</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-move.html"><font size=+1>M</font>OVE&<font size=-1>S</font>CROLL</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-file.html"><font size=+1>F</font>ILE</A>  
X<A HREF="func-custom.html"><font size=+1>C</font>USTOMISATION</A>,  
X<A HREF="func-help.html"><font size=+1>H</font>ELP  
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/left.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT=""></A> 
X<strong><font size=+1>M</font>ISC.</strong>
X
X<HR>
X
X<DL>
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="undo">undo</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Keys</I>: Alt-z, F12
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Edit
X<P>
X<DD>Undo the last editing command.  Undo can be called repeatedly to undo
Xseveral previous changes.  The number of possible undos currently is 40.
XUndos themselves are recorded on the undo-stack and can be undone (redo).
XTo redo, use a non-undo function (e.g. move cursor), then undo again.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="find">find</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-f
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Tools
X<P>
X<DD>Find a word or string in the buffer. Starts a dialog to specify
Xsome options.
X
XThe elements of the find dialog are:
X
X<blockquote>
X<dl>
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>The find string</strong>
X    <dd>Enter here the string to be searched for.
X
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>"Insert" buttons</strong>
X    <dd>Line Break: inserts a line break into the search string. By doing
X	this, strings can be found that contain a line break or are either
X	at the beginning or the end of a line. E.g. by searching for 
X	"abc<em>line break</em>", only strings "abc" at the end of a line will
X	be found.<br>
X	Tab: inserts a Tab character into the search string.
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Case sensitive option</strong>
X    <dd>If checked, this option causes Red to search for the search string with
X	exactly the letter case as you have specified it.  If not checked (the 
X	default), Red finds the search string in any combination of upper and lower
X	case characters.
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Match whole word option</strong>
X    <dd>If checked, only whole words are found.
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Find Forward button</strong>
X    <dd>Clicking this button closes the dialog box and searches for the specified
X	string from the cursor position forward.  This is the default button (a press
X	of the Return key acts as a click in this button).
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Find Backward button</strong>
X    <dd>Closes the dialog box and searches for the specified
X	string from the cursor position backward.
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Help button</strong>
X    <dd>Display a help text for the dialog.
X	
X  <dt><IMG SRC="../graphics/balls/orange.gif"><strong>Close button</strong>
X    <dd>Closes the dialog without performing a search.
X	
X</dl>
X</blockquote>
X
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="find-backward">find-backward</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Shift-Alt-f
X<P>
X<DD>Same as <I>find</I>, but the default button is <I>Find Backward</I>.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="find-next">find-next</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-g
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Tools
X<P>
X<DD>Finds the string currently selected or, if nothing is selected, the same
Xpattern as in the last find operation.  Uses the same parameters (direction,
Xcase sensitivity, whole word option) as the last find operation. Stops at the
Xend of the buffer. If called again, wraps around to the beginning (end) of the
Xbuffer.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="find-next-reverse">find-next-reverse</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Shift-Alt-g
X<P>
X<DD>Like <I>find-next</I>, but reverse the direction of the search.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="replace">replace</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-r
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Tools
X<P>
X<DD>Replace string in the buffer with another one. Starts a dialog to specify some 
Xoptions.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="set-mark">set-mark</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Ctrl-space, F7
X<P>
X<DD>Set the mark at the current cursor position.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="goto-line">goto-line</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: F5
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Tools
X<P>
X<DD>Set cursor to line number. The line number is prompted for after 
Xstarting this command.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="show-line-number">show-line-number</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: F6
X<DD><I>Menu</I>: Tools
X<P>
X<DD>Display the current line number in the information area.
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="define-macro">define-macro</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<P>
X<DD>Record the following keq sequence until the next call to
X<I>end-macro</I> and store it as a macro.
X(NOT YET IMPLEMENTED!)
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="end-macro">end-macro</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<P>
X<DD>End the current macro recording, ask for a key, and bind execution
Xof the macro to that key. (Must be currently defining a macro.
X(NOT YET IMPLEMENTED!)
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="run-macro">run-macro</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<P>
X<DD>...
X<P>
X<HR>
X
X<DT><STRONG><A NAME="redisplay">redisplay</A></STRONG>
X<P>
X<DD><I>Key</I>: Alt-l
X<P>
X<DD>Center cursor in the window and redisplay the screen.
X</DL>
X<HR>
X
X<A HREF="func-edit.html"><font size=+1>E</font>DIT</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-move.html"><font size=+1>M</font>OVE&<font size=-1>S</font>CROLL</A>, 
X<A HREF="func-file.html"><font size=+1>F</font>ILE</A>  
X<A HREF="func-custom.html"><font size=+1>C</font>USTOMISATION</A>,  
X<A HREF="func-help.html"><font size=+1>H</font>ELP  
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/left.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT=""></A> 
X<strong><font size=+1>M</font>ISC.</strong>
X<p>
X
X<A HREF="red-main-page.html">
X   <IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 SRC="../graphics/buttons/back.gif" 
X   border=0 align=middle ALT="">
X   <font size=+1>M</font>AIN <font size=+1>I</font>NDEX</A>
X
X<A HREF="function-group.html">
